    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_3310822489" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3310822489" />
    <a title="Kathy" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/31175766-kathy"><img alt="Kathy" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1543527439p2/31175766.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3310822489?book_show_action=true">Apr 30, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Kathy" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Kathy" href="/user/show/31175766-kathy">Kathy</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9780393349849" href="/book/show/20663749-orfeo">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3310822489" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer8596515977410349664">I wanted to try this author and I like music, so I started out with this choice from 2014 of his many books. I can imagine having this novel used as a text to study within certain college level classes, but it is not a good candidate for leisure reading. I was moved by some of the text and annoyed with quite a few transitions or lack thereof.<br/>I did find playing some Mahler in the background helped a bit.<br/><br/>Library Loan</span>

          </span>
        </div>


