<div id="review_821220784" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/821220784" />
    <a title="Jessica" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/419287-jessica"><img alt="Jessica" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1289534648p2/419287.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/821220784?book_show_action=true">Jan 12, 2014</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Jessica" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Jessica" href="/user/show/419287-jessica">Jessica</a>
      </span>

          marked it as aborted-efforts




        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer821220784" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer16956933137266176627">This is the most excited I&apos;ve been about a new book in a long time. I kept checking at the bookstore to see if it had come in yet, and when I finally got it in my hot grubby hands I was sure I was in for the literary high point of my year. Finally, I thought: Powers has ditched his doomed effort to portray the Everyman and has written a novel about a brilliant, weirdo loner! And with science-something-genes -something -- yay! I was going to love it, just love it, I was sure.<br/><br/>Unfortunately, I foun</span>
  <span id="freeText16956933137266176627" style="display:none">This is the most excited I've been about a new book in a long time. I kept checking at the bookstore to see if it had come in yet, and when I finally got it in my hot grubby hands I was sure I was in for the literary high point of my year. Finally, I thought: Powers has ditched his doomed effort to portray the Everyman and has written a novel about a brilliant, weirdo loner! And with science-something-genes -something -- yay! I was going to love it, just love it, I was sure.<br /><br />Unfortunately, I found it it pretty much unreadable. I'm so bored and miserable while reading that I can't stand to pick it up, but because I committed to it -- and bought it! Full price, in hard cover! And with such blind fannish enthusiasm and high hopes! -- I haven't been able to start anything else.<br /><br />I'm not sure what the problem is, except that I personally find all the music stuff skull-numbingly dull. I guess I was able to put up with it in <i>The Time of Our Singing</i> because I was interested in the characters and story, but here I just kept snoozing off midway down the page. Nothing held me -- not the main guy, nothing that was happening in the plot, not even Powers's writing -- except a depressing sense of obligation.<br /><br />I feel sad about this, but for whatever reason, I just can't engage with this book, so I'm going to set it aside and read something else. I may come back later and love it; sometimes that trick works. But for now I'm going to stop throwing myself up against the wall of this book hoping to stick, because all that's happened is some bruising and headaches and feeling pretty dumb.</span>
  <a data-text-id="16956933137266176627" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


